It’s time for an introduction!! 

Hi to all my beautiful new followers, I’m so happy you’re here :) My name is Suvi, I’m a (fully) Indian woman living in Canada. I was born in India, I love my culture and I’m proud of my heritage. 

My mom says the first word I ever spoke was “mama” but I KNOW the first words that actually came out of my mouth were “Dior lipgloss”. 

I’m in my 20’s (not telling you my exact age ;) and I currently work in the communications strategy field. I’ve been in marketing for some time now, but I also love business!! For the longest time, my goal has been to own my own business in the creative sphere, and I currently own two.

I was also the annoying kid in elementary school who carried around a shitty little camera everywhere. In class, on field trips, in the washroom, you name it. I’ve always had a camera on me :) 

I love fashion, drawing, painting, makeup, writing and cooking. Basically anything creative, I’m all over it. Also coffee and croissants. Also I LOVE animals. Dogs and cats specifically. 

I’m a big extrovert, I’m the happiest when people are having fun with me, but there are nights where I’m happiest snuggling up next to my hunky 6’4 boyfriend (sorry if you’re following me because I’m hot) while watching K-dramas or anime with him. 

Thank you for being on this journey with me :) If you made it all the way to the end, it’s nice to meet you 🥹🌟
grateful every day for this beautiful beautiful life of mine that I’ve built from ground up

Life has been so good to me these last few years 🥺

If you’ve been following me since my university days while I was working at Starbucks you remember how much I hated working there. I’d have days where I’d cry in the back room freezer and days where customers would throw coffee at me because their order “was wrong” 

I’ve worked so damn hard these last few years and every spare minute I’ve had I’ve dedicated to learning new skills. I can’t tell you how much this changed my life!! 

I’m rewatching Suits right now with the love of my life next to me and I’m getting emotional (surprise surprise) because the fruits of my labour are being handed to me these days. 

Not to get super gushy (I’m a gushy human 🥹) but thank you so much for being here, following my journey, and sending me your love. When I say I’m grateful every day that’s not an exaggeration, we are all friends :) 

I wish you so much love and happiness and success this year and every year after that til the end of time. Also whatever it is that you think you can’t do, you probably can. Just keep going and don’t stop :-) 

Yours truly 🎀
